|Example.Gloss=For this question self-1sg sit-1sg-pst see-present(doubt) ke solution-(path-work) in program(plan) see-2ndPl-present prog or no
|Example.English translation=For this question I, myself, searched carefully to know whether there is a solution for the plan or not
|Example.Comments=See is used twice in this example. Only the first usage of see, translated as ‘consider’ is relevant to knowing is seeing. Aria
